<div id="contentIntro" class="sbs-intro">
	<div class="row">





<div class="col col-6">
		<span class="page-count">
			
			6 <span class="page-count-divider">of</span> 7
		</span>
		<h2 class="heading ">The Ghosts and Goblins of the Government Palace, Lima</h2>
</div><div class="keyboard-nav">
	<p>Use <img src="/image/arrow-keys.png" /> to navigate.</p>
</div>	</div>



<figure class="content-img-wrapper">
<div class="sbs-img-frame">
<div class="sbs-prev-next-top">
<div class="page-btns group small">
<div class="col pull-left prev">
<a href="#step5" data-component="stepbystepImage" data-source="stepbystepImage" data-type="" data-ordinal="Prev" class="btn p-b-col ajax-link-sbs"><span class="sprite arrow5-left"></span></a>
</div>
<div class="col pull-right next">
<a href="#step7" data-component="stepbystepImage" data-source="stepbystepImage" data-type="" data-ordinal="Next" class="ajax-link-sbs"></a> <span class="btn p-b-col">
<span class="sprite arrow5-right"></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
</div> <div class="sbs-img-wrapper expandable collapsed">
<div class="content-img-wrapper ">
<div class="image-pinit-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/goperu/1/S/7/D/-/-/government_palace_lima_haunted.jpg" alt="Government Palace, Lima - Frank van den Bergh/E+/Getty Images" class="" data-description="The Most Haunted Places in Peru: The Ghosts and Goblins of the Government Palace, Lima" itemprop="image" >
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://goperu.about.com/od/sightsandattractions/ss/The-Most-Haunted-Places-in-Peru.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/goperu/1/S/7/D/-/-/government_palace_lima_haunted.jpg&description=The Most Haunted Places in Peru: The Ghosts and Goblins of the Government Palace, Lima" data-component="stepbystepImage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="6" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</figure>
<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
<div class="content-img-caption">
Ghosts inhabit the Government Palace, Lima.
<span class="credit">Photo Credit: Frank van den Bergh/E+/Getty Images</span>
</div>
</figcaption></div>	
				<article class="sbs content widget expert-content">
					<div class="expert-content-text">
							<p>We all trust our leaders, right? Well, maybe not, but former President of Peru Alan García is on record stating that Lima’s historic Government Palace is home to at least one supernatural entity.</p><p>In 2011, during the final months of his presidency, García claimed that “strange things” were happening in the palace. In an interview for the program<em> La Noche es Mía</em>, García told a reporter:</p><blockquote><p>“At three in the morning there is a friend from centuries ago who usually wanders the palace, especially the second floor. A governor, someone who was executed.”</p></blockquote>
							<p>He also said that many palace employees reported the presence of a <em>duende </em>-- an elf or goblin -- in the palace garage. Apparently, some of these employees sought assistance due to nervous breakdowns following encounters with this creepy creature.</p>
					</div>
				</article>







